<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 12:30:39 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>Take-Two 似乎解雇了人工智能团队的部分人员，其中包括人工智能主管，具体人数不详。</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/take-two-has-seemingly-laid-off-an-unspecified-portion-of-its-ai-team-including-its-head-of-ai</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 12:30:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/take-two-has-seemingly-laid-off-an-unspecified-portion-of-its-ai-team-including-its-head-of-ai</guid></item><item><title>噪声如何限制当今的量子电路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/how-noise-limits-todays-quantum-circuits</link><description>想象一下，您正在尝试构建一条非常长且复杂的多米诺骨牌链。我们的目标是，每张多米诺骨牌都完美地击中下一张，一路向下，最终产生令人惊叹的结果。量子电路就像多米诺骨牌链：一长串微小的步骤（“操作”）共同作用，以强大的方式共同处理信息。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-noise-limits-todays-quantum-circuits.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 12:15:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/how-noise-limits-todays-quantum-circuits</guid></item><item><title>镱原子钟可以打开基础物理学的新窗口</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/ytterbium-atomic-clock-could-open-a-new-window-on-fundamental-physics</link><description>一个国际物理学家团队首次成功地利用镱原子中罕见的轨道跃迁来创建一种新型原子钟，该原子钟既高度精确，又对基本物理效应极其敏感。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ytterbium-atomic-clock-could-open-a-new-window-on-fundamental-physics.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 12:00:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/ytterbium-atomic-clock-could-open-a-new-window-on-fundamental-physics</guid></item><item><title>来自正性的引力：研究声称，单个大质量自旋 3/2 粒子使引力在逻辑上不可避免</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/gravity-from-positivity-single-massive-spin-3-2-particle-makes-gravity-logically-inevitable-study-claims</link><description>IPhT（CEA、CNRS）和巴塞罗那自治大学的研究人员表明，每当自然界中存在巨大的自旋 3/2 粒子时，引力以及随之而来的超对称性就会成为逻辑必然性。有两个原则就足够了：因果性，即没有任何信号的传播速度能超过光速的事实；以及幺正性，即量子力学中概率守恒的要求。超引力的结构不是假设的：它会自我引导。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/gravity-from-positivity-single-massive-spin-3-2-particle-makes-gravity-logically-inevitable-study-claims2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 11:45:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/gravity-from-positivity-single-massive-spin-3-2-particle-makes-gravity-logically-inevitable-study-claims</guid></item><item><title>地下实验室为暗物质搜寻扫清了关键障碍</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/underground-lab-clears-crucial-hurdle-for-dark-matter-hunt</link><description>澳大利亚探测难以捉摸的暗物质的努力向前迈出了一大步，新的研究证实，斯托尔地下物理实验室（SUPL）深处的宇宙辐射水平足够低，足以支持将于今年晚些时候开始的世界级实验。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/underground-lab-clears-crucial-hurdle-for-dark-matter-hunt2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 11:30:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/underground-lab-clears-crucial-hurdle-for-dark-matter-hunt</guid></item><item><title>紧凑的平面透镜系统可以产生非衍射瓶光束</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/compact-flat-lens-system-can-generate-nondiffracting-bottle-beams</link><description>大多数激光源产生在传播时发散的高斯光束。这种自然扩散限制了它们在需要光在长距离上保持集中的应用中的有效性。为了克服这一挑战，人们开发了结构光束，其振幅、相位和偏振可以被仔细控制。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/compact-flat-lens-system-can-generate-nondiffracting-bottle-beams2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 11:15:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/compact-flat-lens-system-can-generate-nondiffracting-bottle-beams</guid></item><item><title>量子纠错的新方法预示着量子计算的可扩展未来</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/novel-approach-to-quantum-error-correction-portends-a-scalable-future-for-quantum-computing</link><description>悉尼大学的一位量子物理学家开发了一种新的量子纠错方法，可以显着减少构建大规模容错量子计算机所需的物理量子位数量。这项研究由物理学院的 Dominic Williamson 博士共同撰写，题为“通过测量逻辑运算符进行低开销容错量子计算”，并发表在《自然物理学》上。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/novel-approach-to-quantum-error-correction-portends-a-scalable-future-for-quantum-computing2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 11:00:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/novel-approach-to-quantum-error-correction-portends-a-scalable-future-for-quantum-computing</guid></item><item><title>量子相干性可以在现实环境中大规模保留</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/quantum-coherence-could-be-preserved-at-large-scales-in-realistic-environments</link><description>众所周知，量子态非常脆弱，只需通过相互作用、测量和暴露于周围环境就可以被破坏。在发表于的一项新理论研究中&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quantum-coherence-could-be-preserved-at-large-scales-in-realistic-environments2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 10:45:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/quantum-coherence-could-be-preserved-at-large-scales-in-realistic-environments</guid></item><item><title>黑洞和希格斯质量的秘密可能隐藏在七维几何中</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-secrets-of-black-holes-and-the-higgs-mass-could-be-hidden-in-a-7-dimensional-geometry</link><description>现代物理学最大的谜团之一“黑洞信息悖论”可能最终找到了一个优雅的解决方案，而答案也可能揭示基本粒子质量的起源。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-secrets-of-black-holes-and-the-higgs-mass-could-be-hidden-in-a-7-dimensional-geometry.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 10:30:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-secrets-of-black-holes-and-the-higgs-mass-could-be-hidden-in-a-7-dimensional-geometry</guid></item><item><title>微型微波光子探测器可以推进量子技术</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/a-tiny-detector-for-microwave-photons-could-advance-quantum-tech</link><description>检测单个光粒子很困难；检测单个微波光子更加困难。微波光子是 Wi-Fi 和雷达等当前技术中使用的微小电磁辐射包，其携带的能量远少于可见光。它们比光学光子弱约 100,000 倍。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-tiny-detector-for-microwave-photons-could-advance-quantum-tech2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 10:15:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/a-tiny-detector-for-microwave-photons-could-advance-quantum-tech</guid></item></channel></rss>